  -5.270 -8.568 -9.488 -12.566 -11.690 -15.352 -17.269 -19.174
  -19.943 -20.568 -22.015 -25.115 -26.755

# NOTE on rho. The spatial core is cross-implementation exact: bare-model rho
# matches mlsynth to 4 dp (R 0.8492 vs mlsynth 0.8493). In the FULL config the
# rho posterior is only weakly identified -- the AR(1) latent factor and the
# spatial autoregression compete to explain the same cross-sectional co-movement,
# so rho sits on a near-flat ridge. Every full conditional in this R kernel is
# algebraically identical to mlsynth's NumPy sampler, yet the two settle in
# different regions of the ridge (this R helper near rho~0.24, mlsynth near
# rho~0.41), while the ATT -- the estimand -- agrees within ~5%. Against the
# AUTHORS' canonical Rcpp (see benchmarks/cases/spillsynth_sudan) mlsynth's rho
# matches to 0.004; this tutorial helper is an "inspired-by" variant. The
# benchmark therefore cross-checks the identified quantities (bare rho, ATT,
# spillover ranking, SCM nesting) and treats full-model rho as weakly identified.
